resources.string:
This module will hook all methods from "com.android.server.pm.PackageManagerService" when your device booting and load the apps."XSharedPreferences" and "ContentProvider" may didn't work.

So we need to apply for root privilege to create file in "/data/AppsSwitch.json" and read your configure when your device boot.

 App Debuggable is open source.So this behavior is safe.We will not read other files and information on your device.You can visit GitHub and git code to check it from "About" page.
It looks like you don\'t have any permission to crate file on \"/data/\".\n\nPlease check have app get root privilege and switch the application again.
It looks like your device doesn\'t have root or you denied root privilege.\n\n If your device have root.Please go your root manager and allow App Debuggable and try again.
App Debuggable need \"Storage Permission\" to save configure file.
The configuration is not valid.Please switch the application again.
Please wait....\n\nCheck and apply for root access
Easy module which makes the apps debuggable is true
After switch on or off app you may reboot your device to make it effect.
Reboot fails, possibly due to inadequate permissions. You can manually reboot to make your configuration work.
The legal consequences are not related to the developer.
